30. Definition of Runtime Autonomy

Pantheon autonomy is not unrestricted independence.

Pantheon autonomy means:

The ability to choose useful intermediate actions inside a human-authorized mission while remaining bounded by explicit authority, inspectable reasoning, and reversible execution.

This creates initiative without surrendering stewardship.

